values: Sunday really sucked, because I had my first hangover.  I had a headache, and vomited about 4 times, not including the one time I vomited the night before.  So I ended up sleeping most of Sunday, which really helped, but the day still sucked, and at the moment, when I think about alcohol, I want vomit.

So, I just acquired a few new games for my PS2, and they are Star Ocean 3: till the end of time, Final Fantsy 5, Final Fantasy 6, and Lord of the Rings: The Third Age.  Right now I am currently playing Star Ocean 3, and I must say that it is awesome.  while I am talking about video games, Jake showed my the tech demo for the redone Final Fantasy 7 coming out, or hopefully coming out, for the PS3, and I must say that after watching it, I truely wanted to have an orgasm right then and their.  When it comes out, I think that their never be a game that will even come close to being as god like as FF7, because not only will it have an excellent storyline, but it will have orgamsiuc graphics to boot.  So the I am going to get the PS3, even if it is $500, or so I heard, for the purpose of playing FF7.

I have some great quotes for you people to read.  The first one is from Oscar Wilde
"Self-denial is the shining sore on the leprous body of Christianity."

And, the second one is from Albert Einstein
"Only two things are infinite, the universe and human stupidity, and I'm not sure about the former."

These two quotes are so very true, and in my opinion they, in a way, are related, because Christians, or least the highly devout Christians, are stupid.  But, that is only my opinion.

Time to update my journal.  I haven't updated it in a while, so I figured I might as well do it, or someone I know will get on my case about it.  I was in Florida last week, specifically Orlando.  It was a great trip, except for that fact that it rained on us everyday except the last day.  Last Thursday, I had a rendezvous with Captain Morgan and Bacardi.  That was a great night, and no I did not have a hang over the next morning or vomit.  Let see, I had about a quarter of a bottle of Captain Morgan, and a bottle and a half of Bacardi.  The only bad part about the trip was the bus ride.  36 hours on a bus is not fun, especially if you are trying to sleep.  The that I enjoyed the most about the trip was when we went this place called the Medieval Times for dinner.  There we where lords and ladies and were seated in a stadium, where we had dinner, which we ate like they did in the Medieval times, while watching a jousting tournament.  That was an awesome night also.  So yeah, thats about all I can think to type about.  KE KE KE KE!

I would just like to make this clear about myself, and this is also in response to the James's lj about Sony incorporating the ability to order pizza online while playing Everquest 2.  I have given up all hope on humanity, its just going down the shitter.  We dont seem to realize that tearing down rainforests is actually a bad thing. 
  I know that this makes me sound like a cold hearted bastard, but I didn't the Tsunami disaster.  I thought it was their own fault for living in that part of the world, and that their was more then enough people living there
  I also view humanity as the aliens from Independence Day, because all we are doing is sucking up the resources of this planet, killing it, and when it dies, we will just move on to another planet, and the process will start all over.  So, I think we are just a plague on this world.

SO, I had to play a gig, with the jazz band, for Hopelodge benefit ceremony.  So we played at a church, and now I feel tainted from all that religion.  The whole time we were playing, I just wanted to get the hell out of there.  Dungeons and Dragons this morning was awesome.  You cannot go wrong with a chaotic neutral party.  God that was so much fun.  We need to keep that campaign alive.  I thought we were goona die trying to kill that Captain.  I was waiting for someone to make a terrible roll.  
But, nobody did and we killed him and it was all good.  So.....ke ke ke ke!

Toady really sucked.  Lets see, I'm sick, I been sleeping like crap for the past couple of days, and I have homework to do on top of that.  Life sucks, but like thats a big surprise.  I've always known that life sucks, but i just had to say.  Other than that, in FF10, I fought Biran and Yenke Ronso, with just Kimahri today. Jake, you were wrong about that battle being hard, I thought it was more of just a pain in the ass, and it took way to long.  But going up Mount Gagazet, that I f***in hated.  And thats it for my rant for today.

Theirs not much to say about today.  I got up, had breakfast and played Final Fantasy 10.  I am about to fight Seymour for the second time, and I am not really looking forward to the fight.  But if I have to fight, then I have to fight him.
